fleece /fliːs/

(fleecing,fleeced,fleeces) 

1. N-COUNT A sheep's fleece is the coat of wool that covers it. 羊毛 

例： ...a special protein which triggers the animal to shed its fleece. …一种能够促使这种动物脱毛的特殊蛋白质。 

2. N-COUNT A fleece is the wool that is cut off one sheep in a single piece. (从一只羊身上剪下连在一起的) 羊毛 

例： Wool can be spun from fleeces. 羊毛可以纺成毛线。 

3. V-T If you fleece someone, you get a lot of money from them by tricking them or charging them too much. 诈骗 [非正式] 

例： She claims he fleeced her out of thousands of dollars. 她声称他诈骗了她几千美元。 

4. N-VAR Fleece is a soft warm artificial fabric. A fleece is also a jacket or other garment made from this fabric. 仿毛织物; 绒毛衣物 

例： ...white leather slippers with fleece lining. …带有绒毛衬里的白色皮拖鞋。

